OL,6,FThe NAO noted the so-called "cliff
OL,7,Fedge" created by the current rules,
OL,8,Fmeaning a claimant ` who by law must
OL,9,Finform DWP promptly if their
OL,10,Fcircumstances change ` is either
OL,11,Fentitled to the whole allowance or
OL,12,Fnone of it, and said this can "quickly
OL,13,Fbuild up significant overpayments".
OL,15,FThe report stated: "This means it is
OL,16,Fimportant to identify an overpayment
OL,17,Fearly or, better still, prevent it
OL,18,Ffrom occurring."
